definition.value: A quaternary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of sphingomyelin d18:1, obtined by protonation of the anionic phosphate function.

A sialononaosylceramide having alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialononaosyl component.
A ganglioside in which the oligosaccharide portion is composed of a nonasaccharide, to which one or more sialic acid residues are attached.

A glycononaosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycononaosyl component.
A glycoheptaosylceramide having beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycoheptaosyl component.
An ammonium ion that is obtained by protonation of the amino group of D-glucosylsphingosine. Major species at pH 7.3.
A glycoheptaosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycoheptaosyl component.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the primary amino group of 7-(3-methylbut-2-enyl)-L-tryptophan. Major species at pH 7.3.
A glycohexaosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycohexaosyl component.
Any branched-chain fatty acid containing methyl branches only.
Tetraanion of methacrylyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions; principal microspecies at pH 7.3.
The dicarboxylic acid dianion formed from folic acid by loss of a proton from each of the two carboxy groups in the glutamic acid moiety.

A seven-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp having a beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc attached at the 6-position of the central galactosyl residue.
A linear amino hexasaccharide made up from two glucosamine, one glucose and three galactose residues, linked as shown.
The carotenol formed by demethylation of the carotenoid ether spheroidene.
A linear amino hexasaccharide made up from alternating galactose and glucosamine units linked by alternating beta-(1->4)- an d beta-(1->3)-linkages.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine at the reducing end having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 3-position and an alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 4-position.
Any sesquiterpenoid having a eudesmane skeleton.
An alpha-D-glucoside that is the alpha-D-glucoside of the secondary hydroxy group of D-glyceric acid.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is obtained by removal of a proton from the carboxyl group of 2-O-(alpha-D-glucopyranosyl)-D-glyceric acid.
An amino disaccharide consisting of D-galactose having an alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl residue attached at the 6-position

A linear amino pentasaccharide consisting of the tetrasaccharide beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having an alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl residue attached at the 3-position of the galactosyl residue at the non-reducing end.
A eudesmane sesquiterpenoid in which the eudesmane skeleton carries a hydroxy substituent at C-11 and has a double bond between C-4 and C-5.
A eudesmane sesquiterpenoid in which the eudesmane skeleton carries a hydroxy substituent at C-11, has a double bond between C-4 and C-5 and has inversion of configuration at C-10.
A amino trisaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
A amino trisaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 3-position.
A tricarboxylic acid trianion resulting from the removal of a proton from each of the carboxy groups of tricarballylic acid.
A glycoside consisting of N-acetyl-D-galactosaminitol having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 3-position.

A pentol that is (3S,5R,10R,12S,14S,15R,16R)-12,16-dimethylicosane-3,5,10,14,15-pentol in which the pro-S hydrogen at position 2 is substituted by an amino group. It results from hydrolysis of the O-acyl bonds of fumonisin B1.
A linear amino hexasaccharide consisting of two galactosyl, one glucosamine, two fucose and one glucose residue (at the reducing end) linked as shown.
Permithrin in which the 2,2-dichlorovinyl group and the carboxylate ester group are in a trans-configuration.
The monocarboxylic acid anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of 2-O-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-3-hydroxydecanoyl-3-hydroxydecanoic acid; principal microspecies at pH 7.3.
trans-Permethrin with configuration 1S,3R.
A penicilloate anion arising from deprotonation of both carboxy groups of a penicilloic acid.

An alpha-L-fucoside comprising D-glucitol having an alpha-L-fucosyl group attached at the 3-position as well as a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of (2S,3S,5R,10R,12S,14S,15R,16R)-2-amino-12,16-dimethylicosane-3,5,10,14,15-pentol. Major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of benzyl alcohols that is benzyl alcohol bearing a phenoxy substituent at C-3. It is a metbaolite of the insecticide permethrin.
3-(2,2-Dichlorovinyl)-2,2-dimethylcyclopropanecarboxylic acid with configuration 1S,3R.
A glycoside consisting of D-glucitol having a alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->4)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
An  alpha-amino acid that is 2,7-diaminoheptanoic acid substituted by a imino group at position 7 (the 2S stereoisomer).
An EC 2.3.1.* (acyltransferase transferring other than amino-acyl group) inhibitor that interferes with the action of sphingosine N-acyltransferase (EC 2.3.1.24).
The monocarboxylic acid anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of (1S,3R)-3-(2,2-dichlorovinyl)-2,2-dimethylcyclopropanecarboxylic acid; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A branched seven-membered glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-D-glucose moiety with the galactosyl residue having a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl group attached at the 3-position and an alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl group at the 6-position.
A galactooligosaccharide comprised of repeating alpha-D-galacturonide residues

A branched amino pentasaccharide consisting of the trisaccharide beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactose where the galactosyl residue at the non-reducing end has alpha-L-fucosyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residues attached at the 2- and 3-positions respectively.

A branched amino pentasaccharide consisting of the trisaccharide beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactose where the galactosyl residue at the non-reducing end has alpha-L-fucosyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residues attached at the 2- and 3-positions respectively and the glucosaminyl residue has an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 4-position.
An organophosphate oxoanion derived from deprotonation of the phosphate group of any N-acylphosphatidylethanolamine.

A branched amino pentasaccharide consisting of the trisaccharide beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galctose where the galactosyl residue at the non-reducing end has alpha-L-fucosyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residues attached at the 2- and 3-positions respectively.

A branched amino hexasaccharide consisting of the trisaccharide beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactose where the galactosyl residue at the non-reducing end has alpha-L-fucosyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminylresidues attached at the 2- and 3-positions respectively and the glucosaminyl residue has an alpha-L-fucosyl attached at the 3-position.

A glycooctaosylceramide having alpha-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycooctaosyl component
